data.title: Oracle Support
data.text:
UW Oracle Resource List

Database Office

The Database Office is a unit within the Department of Application and Database Services in the Division of Information Technology.

Our office ensures that the databases, which are the backbone of the administrative applications supported by ADS, are stable, secure, functioning optimally and are backed up to speed disaster recovery.

Oracle Server Software, Client Software, Electronic Documentation, and Hard Copy Documentation:

The University has an enterprise license for the Oracle database software. It can be used for most administrative or academic purposes free of charge to UW customers.

Department of Application and Database Services:

Librarian: 766-5745

Information Security: 766-5747

On-Campus Database Support:

ADS-supported application databases are supported by the Database Office. Support on a paid consultation basis is available from the Database Office for UW administrative- or academic-related purposes.
